{"key":"processedPost-12809697","value":{"id":12809697,"first":12802550,"last":12809905,"when":1277605486,"utime":"06/27/10 05:24 AM","content":"You ideally don't want the weight to rattle.&nbsp; When it does, it means you're releasing <i>excess</i> pressure.&nbsp; Control pressure with the stove burner, not the rocker, to keep water from boiling out.<br />You also should be using a trivet or a row of jar lid rings to keep the substrates off the bottom, not a towel.&nbsp; There's a lot of ghetto things that get recommended around here, and the towel on the bottom is one of them.&nbsp; You can easily fry your jars that way.&nbsp; If you're doing 1/2 pint brf/pf jars, they should be elevated totally out of the water, which might take two rows of jar lid rings.<br />RR","title":"Re: PC ran out of water"}}